	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26-9. Refunding bonds.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26-10. Termination or dissolution.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26-11. Treasurer to determine financial advisor.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26-12. Governor to determine bond counsel.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26-13. Approval and payment of all necessary expenses.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26-14. Dedication of tax.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h2 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs317696C1">article 26a. roads to prosperity state road bonds.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-1. Definitions.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-2. State road general obligation bonds; amount; when may issue.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-3. Creation of debt service fund to pay debt service on state road general obligation bonds.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-4. Roads to Prosperity Bond Debt Service Fund; sources used to pay bonds, interest and cost of issuance; investment of remainder.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-5. Covenants of state.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-6. Sale by Governor; certification of annual debt service amount.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-7. Conflicts of interest.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-8. State road bonds lawful investments.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-9. Refunding bonds.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-10. Termination or dissolution.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-11. Treasurer to determine financial advisor.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-12. Governor to determine bond counsel.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-13. Approval of and payment of all necessary expenses.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;17-26A-14. Dedication of taxes and fees.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><p class="cs55F91DED"><span class="csE736517A">&nbsp;</span></p><h1 class="cs4B09651A">
		<span class="csEEC52858">CHAPTER 31. CORPORATIONS.</span></h1>
	<h2 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs317696C1">ARTICLE 15B. INFRASTRUCTURE BONDS.</span></h2>
	<h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-1. Definitions.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-2. Infrastructure general obligation bonds; amount; when may issue.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-3. Creation of debt service fund; disbursements to pay debt service on infrastructure general obligation bonds.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-4. Infrastructure general obligation debt service fund; sources used to pay bonds and interest; investment of remainder.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-5. Covenants of state.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-6. Sale by Governor; minimum price.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-7. Prohibition on funds inuring to the benefit of or being distributable to directors or officers; transactions between the council and West Virginia water development authority and directors or officers having certain interests in such transactions.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-8. Infrastructure bonds lawful investments.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-9. Refunding bonds.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-10. Termination or dissolution.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-11. Treasurer to determine financial advisor.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-12. Governor to determine bond counsel.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><h4 class="csCA36641A">
		<span class="cs6D9F0C8B">&sect;31-15B-13. Approval and payment of all necessary expenses.</span></h4>
	<p class="cs45E53620"><span class="csE736517A">[Repealed.]</span></p><p class="csDE8452F9"><span class="csAD690475"><br/>NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to require State Treasurer approval to issue refunding bonds; to set forth the process by which general obligation bonds authorized by the West Virginia Constitution shall be issued and administered in the future; and to relocate all provisions concerning outstanding general obligation bonds to a single chapter of the West Virginia Code.</span></p><p class="csDE8452F9"><span class="csAD690475">Strike&#8209;throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added.</span></p>


</div>
 
 
